libsecprog
------------------------------------------
The Secure Programming Library provides several functions that should serve as
a replacement for problematic C functions from glibc. Besides the replacement
functions there are some helper-functions (like: safe_reopen() or
sigprotection()) that can be used for developing exposed applications.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libsecprog-devel-0.8-1bl1
  libsecprog0-0.8-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://users.suse.com/~thomas/projects/secproglib/

Canonical download:
  http://users.suse.com/~thomas/projects/secproglib/libsecprog-0.8-5.1.src.rpm

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsecprog-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsecprog-0.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsecprog-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsecprog-0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsecprog0-0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsecprog-devel-0.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsecprog)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsecprog.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsecprog/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libsecprog/COPYING
  /usr/share/man/man3/secprog.3.gz

(libsecprog0)
  /usr/bin/cygsecprog-0.dll

(libsecprog-devel)
  /usr/include/secprog.h
  /usr/lib/libsecprog.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsecprog.pc

------------------

